@*
    Example 3 — Custom glyph via ChildContent.

    ChildContent REPLACES THE GLYPH INSIDE THE BUTTON. It does not render
    the list items — those come from Targets. The fragment receives a
    ShareButtonContext of { Open, Url }, so the face can react to the
    open state and can show what will be shared.

    Two rules survive the override:

    1. Keep the replacement decorative — aria-hidden="true" on whatever
       you render. The accessible name is Label, and Label alone. If the
       glyph is exposed to assistive tech it competes with the label and
       screen readers may read both.

    2. Do not put interactive content inside it. The fragment renders
       inside the <button>; a nested button or link is invalid HTML and
       breaks keyboard behaviour.

    The default ↪ (U+21AA) is an in-font arrow, so it renders in the
    page's own font and stays monochrome. Override it when your font
    stack lacks the character, or when your design language calls for an
    inline SVG — not to swap in an emoji, which will render as a colour
    pictograph on some platforms and a monochrome glyph on others.
*@

@page "/examples/share-button/custom-glyph"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using LilyDesignSystem.Blazor.Helpers

<ShareButton Label="Share this page" Targets="@Targets" CopyLabel="Copy link"
             CopiedLabel="Link copied"
             CopyFailedLabel="Could not copy — copy it from the address bar">
    @* An inline SVG: no bundled icon asset, and it inherits currentColor. *@
    <svg class="my-share-icon" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"
         width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16"
         style="@(context.Open ? "transform: rotate(90deg)" : null)">
        <path fill="currentColor"
              d="M9 1v3C4 4 1 7 1 12c1.5-2.5 4-3.5 8-3.5V12l6-5.5L9 1z" />
    </svg>
</ShareButton>

@code {
    private static readonly ShareTarget[] Targets =
    {
        new()
        {
            Id = "mastodon",
            Label = "Mastodon",
            Href = (url, title, _) =>
                $"https://mastodon.social/share?text={Uri.EscapeDataString(title)}%20{Uri.EscapeDataString(url)}",
        },
    };
}
